@section styles {
    <style>
        .nuget-badge code {
            -moz-border-radius: 5px;
            -webkit-border-radius: 5px;
            border-radius: 5px;
            background-color: #202020;
            border: 4px solid silver;
            border-radius: 5px;
            box-shadow: 2px 2px 3px #6e6e6e;
            color: #e2e2e2;
            display: block;
            font: 1.1em 'andale mono', 'lucida console', monospace;
            line-height: 1.5em;
            overflow: auto;
            padding: 15px
        }
    </style>
}

<h3>@ViewBag.Title</h3>

<p>You can download jQuery Validation Unobtrusive Native from <a href="http://www.nuget.org/packages?q=jQuery.Validation.Unobtrusive.Native" target="_blank">NuGet</a>.  For an MVC 4 project go <a href="http://www.nuget.org/packages/jQuery.Validation.Unobtrusive.Native.MVC4/" target="_blank">here</a> or run the following command in the Package Manager Console:</p>

<div class="nuget-badge">
    <p><code>PM&gt; Install-Package jQuery.Validation.Unobtrusive.Native.MVC4</code></p>
</div>

<p>For an MVC 3 project go <a href="http://www.nuget.org/packages/jQuery.Validation.Unobtrusive.Native.MVC3/" target="_blank">here</a> or run the following command in the Package Manager Console:</p>

<div class="nuget-badge">
    <p><code>PM&gt; Install-Package jQuery.Validation.Unobtrusive.Native.MVC3</code></p>
</div>

<p>For all intents and purposes the 2 packages are identical.  The MVC 4 package has one extra parameter available for <code>TextBoxFor</code> which it shipped as part of MVC 4 but that should be the only difference.</p>

<p>If you want to get the source, it can be found on <a href="http://github.com/johnnyreilly/jQuery.Validation.Unobtrusive.Native" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.</p>

